<HEADLINE> Kuwait, Tunis Resume Flight After Seven Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 25 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait will resume
air-links with Tunis starting from Sunday after seven years of
suspension since the Gulf War in 1991, a statement of the
state-owned Kuwait Airways Corporation declared today.
</P>
<P>
The corporation's director of public relations Abdallah Saud
Al-Nafisi said in the statement an Airbus-310 plane would
depart Kuwait to Tunis at 9:30 every Sunday and would
proceed to Casablanca, Morocco.
</P>
<P>
The plane would fly back to Kuwait via Tunis Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
