<HEADLINE> 3 Palestinian Youths Wounded in Rallies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 25 (Xinhua) -- Three Palestinian youths were
wounded during clashes with Israeli soldiers who fired tear gas
and rubber bullets.
</P>
<P>
They were among hundreds of Palestinians demonstrating in West
Bank and East Jerusalem to demand the release of Palestinian
political prisoners jailed by Israel.
</P>
<P>
The three were suffering from the effects of tear gas fired by
Israeli soldiers guarding the Jewish holy site Rachel Tomb in the
West Bank city Bethlehem.
</P>
<P>
The protesters were marching toward the tomb and threw stones
at Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Demonstrations were also held in East Jerusalem and other West
Bank cities of Nablus, Hebron and Tulkam, but no clashes occurred
during the protests.
</P>
<P>
Israel is currently holding about 5,000 Palestinian prisoners,
whose future will be settled through negotiations between Israel
and the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) on implementing their
1995 interim accords.
</P>
<P>
The peace have just been resumed after a seven-month deadlock
resulting from Israel's intransigence in building a Jewish
settlement in traditionally Arab East Jerusalem in March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
