<DOCNO> XIE19971026.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Grants Six Locomotives to Tanzania-Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 25 (Xinhua) -- China granted today six
brand-new locomotives to the Tanzania Zambia Railway Authority
(TAZARA) in a drive to reinvigorate the major traffic line
between the two African countries.
</P>
<P>
The six sets of 3,000 horse power diesel electric locomotives
have been provided in accordance with an agreement reached by the
governments of China, Tanzania and Zambia in August of 1995.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a ceremony to hand over the locomotives,
Tanzania's Minister of Communications and Transport, William
Kusila, said that the locomotives will inject vitality into the
railway whose performance has deteriorated over the past few
years.
</P>
<P>
He urged railway workers to work with the new management of
TAZARA so that "the use of the six new locomotives can go towards
stopping this continued deterioration in performance."
</P>
<P>
A delegate from Zambia expressed her wish to turn the railway
into an investment corridor. "We will endeavor to ensure
investment in this corridor becomes a reality so that more
traffic will be generated," she said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese ambassador Zhang Hongxi said the railway crystallizes
the friendship between the three peoples of Tanzania, Zambia and
China.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume between China and Tanzania had exceeded 60
million US dollars by the end of September, 15 percent over the
same period of last year, said a Chinese business official.
</P>
<P>
Yang Chanxing, deputy chief engineer of the manufacturer
Dalian Locomotive and Rolling Stock Works, said that the
locomotives have experimented for one month before the handover.
</P>
<P>
TAZARA officials have expressed satisfaction over the
performance of the locomotives, he said.
</P>
<P>
The 1860-km-long railway, streching from Tanzanian capital of
Dar es Salaam to Kapiri Mposhi of Zambia, traverses mountains,
valleys and marshland. It was built from October of 1970 to July
of 1976 under the aid of the Chinese government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
