<HEADLINE> Khatami Lashes US Military Presence in Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 25 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami today indirectly attacked the United States, saying "the
era of securing interests through force and aggression is over."
</P>
<P>
Meeting with visiting Kuwait Minister of Social Affairs and
Labor Ahmad Khaled Al-Kulaib, the president reiterated foreign
presence is a threat to security of the region.
</P>
<P>
"The countries and forces which consider using force to achieve
their interests in the region are making a grave mistake," Khatami
said, quoted by the official news agency of IRNA.
</P>
<P>
He said that such a mistake is a source of great harm to
humanity, adding "world stability cannot be founded on aggression."
</P>
<P>
"Not only the nations won't submit to aggression, but also the
world public opinion would never condones it," he added.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has about 20,000 soldiers with its Fifth Fleet in the
Gulf and it recently sent aircraft carrier Nimitz, which has about
80 tactical aircraft on board, and its combat group of seven
destroyers, four frigates, an attack submarine and two
minesweepers to reinforce its military presence.
</P>
<P>
Khatami said the region belongs to regional countries and they
should cooperate in achieving security. "The situation is ripe to
bind an accord amongst regional countries based on mutual respect,
an accord which addresses the interests of all the states in the
region," he added.
</P>
<P>
Citing Palestinian struggle as a clear evidence of a nation's
steadfast resistance to aggression, Khatami said "we must endeavor
to build a future based on understanding and dialog and always
confront the hegemonic powers."
</P>
<P>
He said that addressing world and regional problems through
negotiations is the cornerstone of Iran's foreign policy and Iran
is ready to cooperate with regional countries in this regard.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwait minister, who arrived in Tehran Friday to deliver a
message from the Kuwait Emir to Khatami, described relations
between the two countries as satisfactory.
</P>
<P>
"The many meetings and negotiations between high ranking
officials of the two countries are evidences of progressive
relations between the two neighbors," he said.
</P>
<P>
He praised Iran's opposition to the Iraqi occupation of Kuwait
seven years ago, saying "Kuwait will never forget Iran's
humanitarian assistance during those tough and critical years."
</P>
</TEXT>
