<HEADLINE> 48 Killed in Road Accident in Central Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 25 (Xinhua) -- Forty-eight people were killed
in a serious traffic accident in central Turkey earlier today,
local TV and radio reports said.
</P>
<P>
An empty oil truck drove into the wrong direction and ran into
a coach fully loaded with passengers on a highway near Konya city,
some 210 kilometers south of the capital Ankara, police said.
</P>
<P>
It took the firefighters more than one hour to put under
control the flames caused by the collision. Rescue workers said
most victims were burned to death and beyond recognition.
</P>
<P>
Five injured passengers, three in serious condition, were
rushed to a nearby hospital for emergency treatment.
</P>
<P>
The highway linking Konya and eastern city of Kayseri was
closed for four hours due to the accident.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is among the countries with the worst traffic
accidents. A total of 220,798 road accidents were reported in the
first seven months of this year, claiming 2,713 lives. 
</P>
