The restrictions imposed on Iraq were supposed to have been
eased, but what happened was that these restrictions are getting
harder despite Iraq's cooperation with the UNSCOM, AL-Jomhouria
complained.
</P>
<P>
It asked U.N. Security Council members to come to a conclusion
on what Iraq has accomplished, through studying the reports of the
UNSCOM and their embassies in Baghdad.
