<HEADLINE> Villeneuve Claims F-1 Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, October 26 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Jacques Villeneuve was
third in the last leg of the European Grand Prix in Jerez, Spain,
on Sunday but claimed this year's Formular One world championships
for Williams team.
</P>
<P>
Mika Hakkinen of Finland completed the 4,428 kilometers circuit
running first with a time of one hour, 38 minutes and 57.772
seconds. His McLaren teammate David Coulthard of Britain finished
second with 1.654 seconds late while Villeneuve 1.802 seconds late.
</P>
<P>
German Michael Schumacher failed to make his third world
championships title for Ferrari after withdrawing in the 48th lap
as he clashed upon Villeneuve's Williams.
</P>
<P>
Schumacher made a flying start and led all the way before the
collasion.
</P>
<P>
The German led this season in the points before the final
showdown with Villeneuve, who was one point behind after he was
cut out two points in Japan leg when he didn't slow down before
yellow flag.
</P>
<P>
This was the 11th victory for the Williams driver this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
