<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The close circuit television
system has been adopted for traffic management in Nepal's capital
city, the official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
This system is installed at the Kathmandu Valley Traffic Police
control room.
</P>
<P>
Video cameras installed at some major places of Kathmandu are
currently connected with cables, but the wireless system will be
adopted in the next phase, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The project cost 2.4 million rupees (about 41,380 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Nepali Police Chief Dhruba Bahadur Pradhan said that the system
will be extended to the entire Kathmandu Valley in the future.
</P>
