<HEADLINE> Dam Narrows Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI, October 26 (Xinhua) -- Four hours after the damming
operation was launched, the flow width of the Yellow River,
China's second longest, was narrowed from 106 meters to 83.64
meters.
</P>
<P>
The operation for the Xiaolangdi Water Control Project started
at 4:15 p.m. today. The damming will take a total of 42 hours to
complete.
</P>
<P>
According to Wu Xi, who is in charge of the damming, the
operation is well underway, with 33 large trucks dumping about
3,000 cubic meters of stone into the river each hour.
</P>
<P>
"The river flow is not strong, and it is good for the damming
operation, which is expected to be completed a little bit ahead of
schedule," Wu said.
</P>
<P>
The work will continue round-the-clock, until the two sides of
the dam are joined at 10 a.m. on October 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
