<HEADLINE> Comprehensive Development of Agriculture Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 26 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official today
stressed the importance of comprehensive development in
agriculture while visiting an agriculture exhibition here.
</P>
<P>
The full-scale development, which has been successful in the
past ten years, should be continued and promoted, said Tian Jiyun,
vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks during a visit to the Exhibition on Ten
Years' Achievements of the National Comprehensive Development in
Agriculture, which attracted 31 units with about 60,000 kinds of
products on display.
</P>
<P>
Tian said more than 13 million hectares of high-yield land has
been cultivated, since the comprehensive development program was
launched in the 1980s, which means an increase of 40 percent in
the national grain output capacity.
</P>
<P>
The program was a major strategic measure to stablize and raise
the fluctuating grain output volume through issuing preferential
policies for agriculture and launching state agricultural
projects. 
</P>
