Neither side had a clear chance in the second half and the UAE
were content to keep the frustrated Japanese at bay.
</P>
<P>
Japan will take on South Korea in Seoul on November 1, while
the Emirates play Uzbekistan at home on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
After six matches, South Korea leads the five nation group with
16 points. UAE placed second with eight points and Japan third
with seven points. Kazakhstan has six points and Uzbekistan five.
</P>
