<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Councillor on Socialist Cultural Undertakings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) should be used as a guide for
navigating the development path of the country's socialist
cultural undertakings and meeting the public's increasing demand
for cultural pursuits, State Councillor Li Tieying said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a forum on cultural work in the capital city of
southwest China's Sichuan Province, Li said that the Party
congress has clearly defined the status, nature, objectives, and
major content and tasks of socialist culture with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the guiding principle of the congress concerning
cultural undertakings is of practical use, and priority should be
placed on studying and carrying out the guidelines of the congress
in daily life, said Li, who is also member of the Political Bureau
of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping's theory on cultural undertakings is an important
component of Deng Xiaoping Theory as a whole and has become the
guide for cultural development, Li said, adding that thriving
cultural and arts projects must serve the people and socialism. He
noted that China has many flourishing and competitive schools for
the arts.
</P>
<P>
The socialist culture should be inspiring, reflect people's
real life and emphasize social benefits rather than economic
returns, Li said.
</P>
<P>
To advance cultural undertakings with Chinese characteristics
throughout China's primary stage of socialism is necessary to
achieve coordinated economic, political and cultural development
of the country and meet the people's increasing demand for a
better cultural life, he added.
</P>
<P>
Since the country's reform and opening-up, cultural
undertakings have entered a booming period. However, they still
cannot satisfy the wants of the people who are beginning to enjoy
a fairly comfortable life, Li said.
</P>
<P>
More attention should be paid to updating the theory on
cultural undertakings, enlist more people to join cultural
circles, promote the cultural productions, and better manage
cultural undertakings, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that in a socialist market economy, reform is the
way to ensure the success of cultural undertakings, including the
reform of state-owned performance organizations and a wider
opening of cultural facilities to the public. 
</P>
</TEXT>
