<HEADLINE> Russia, China Win in Dalian Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 26 (Xinhua/OANA) -- Russian Shalameyef Sergei
and Chinese Dong Yanmei, who broke the world women's 5,000m record
twice at China's eighth games in Shanghai last week, won the
Dalian international marathon race on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian runner timed two hour, 19 minutes and 41 seconds
for the men's victory, followed by China's Sun Chang from
Heilongjiang Province in 2:19:44.
</P>
<P>
Hu Gangjun, winner of the Beijing marathon on October 4 in
2:09:18, finished third in 2:19:51.
</P>
<P>
In the women's competition, Dong, who also took the women's
10,000m in 30:38.09 at the national games ended last Friday,
clocked two hours, 28 minutes and 09 seconds for the marathon
title here.
</P>
<P>
Dong, coached by Ma Junren of Liaoning middle and long distance
team, looked no fatigue after her astonishing races in Shanghai
where she broke the 5,000m world record in heats and finals along
with her teammate Jiang Bo, who won the 5,000m with a new mark of
14:28.09.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yanrong and Sun Yingjie, both from China, took second and
third in 2:28:41 and 2:30:10 respectively.
</P>
<P>
More than 700 runners, including 88 foreigners from Russia,
Japan, South Korea, Poland, Kenya and so on, took part in the
annual race which started in 1987. 
</P>
