<HEADLINE> Fuzhou-Macao and Xiamen-Macao Flights Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, October 26 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen Airlines has opened two
new flights, between Macao and Fuzhou, the capital of east China's
Fujian province, and between Macao and Xiamen, the provincial
special economic zone.
</P>
<P>
Both flights will operate round-trip once a day. For the first
time, the company has used its own flight identification -- MF --
since it gained the right to run international flights in January
1996.
</P>
<P>
In August 1996, Xiamen Aviation Company launched the Fuzhou to
Macao route by chartered planes in cooperation with an aviation
company from Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen Airlines is China's first regional civil aviation
enterprise. It is jointly-run by the Civil Aviation Administration
of China (CAAC) and the aviation office of Fujian province.
</P>
<P>
Altogether, the company operates 16 Boeing airplanes and has
opened more than 80 domestic flights since it was established in
1984. The company transports over three million passengers every
year.
</P>
<P>
So far, it registers a total capital of four billion yuan (500
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Sources said that the company would continue to cooperate with
aviation companies from Taiwan and Macao, which would in turn
contribute to their economic development.
</P>
<P>
Additionally, tourists from Hong Kong and Southeast Asia could
travel back and forth from Fuzhou and Xiamen via Macao. 
</P>
