<HEADLINE> Macao to Open Up Mobile Phone Service Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 26 (Xinhua) -- Macao plans to open up its mobile
 phone service market early next year, and two to three mobile
phone service companies are expected to gain operation rights.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Lopes, director of the Macao Posts and
Telecommunications Department, told the Tai Chung Pou newspaper
that a set of new telecommunications regulations are being
formulated to open up the mobile phone service market.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Telecommunications Company (CTM), which currently
monopolizes the local market under agreement with the government,
will only run the domestic telephone and long distance telephone
services in the future, he said.
</P>
<P>
The new regulations, upon approval by the Sino-Portuguese Joint
 Liaison Group (JLG), is expected to be promulgated and come into
effect early next year, he said, adding that the government will
add two to three more operators of the mobile phone service
through public bidding.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the cost of using mobile phone service will drop
markedly.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the director said that his department is
negotiating with the CTM on the further reduction of the price of
long distance calls, which has drawn lots of complaints. He said
the price cut may start next January.
</P>
<P>
The losses CTM will suffer due to the opening of mobile phone
service will be compensated through extending its monopoly terms,
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
