<HEADLINE> Historic Visit to Push Forward Sino-US Relations: Macao Papers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The historic visit by China's
President Jiang Zemin to the United States will help push forward
the cooperative relations between the two countries, a commentary
in today's Macao Daily News said.
</P>
<P>
The first visit to the U.S. by a Chinese state leader in 12
years marks the entry of a new relationship built on a strategic
basis, the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
The strategic basis, it said, means that the two sides share
many bilateral common interests and a "wide range of common
strategic interests."
</P>
<P>
Those interests involve such hot topics as world peace and
development, the establishment of a new world order, disarmament,
non-proliferation of nuclear weapons and weapons of mass
destruction, environmental protection, anti-terrorism, and the
settlement of regional disputes, among others.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that close cooperation between the two
countries is needed if those issues are to be addressed
effectively.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a huge potential in cooperation in the economic
and trade field has laid down a strong economic foundation for the
"common strategic interests," it said.
</P>
<P>
While giving prominent coverage to Jiang's visit, the paper
said the upcoming summit meeting between China and the U.S. would
pave the way for a framework of new relations that will last to
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Tai Chung Pou newspaper said that President
Jiang's visit to the U.S. will have significant and far-reaching
influence on the Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese-language newspaper said because the two sides
share many common interests, they should seek cooperation and
develop relationship by seeking common ground while putting aside
differences in ideology and political system.
</P>
<P>
"A new type of strategic partnership relations between China
and the U.S. will be a decisive factor for the peace and
development of the Asia-Pacific region and the entire world in the
21st century," it said. "That will also be happy news for mankind."
</P>
<P>
The Correio Sino-Macaense newspaper predicts that the Sino-U.S.
summit will help resolve the Taiwan issue, which it said is the
most important and most sensitive part of the Sino-U.S.
relationship.
</P>
<P>
"The summit meeting will make the U.S. side reiterate its
political promise of upholding the 'one China' policy, and keep to
the spirit and principles laid down in the three joint
communiques," it said.
</P>
<P>
"Under these circumstances, the cross-straits relations will
continue to ease up for quite a long time," the newspaper added.
"That will help create an environment for the political dialog
across the Taiwan Straits and the final reunification of China."
</P>
</TEXT>
