<HEADLINE> Sydney Games Triathlon Course Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The 2000 Olympic Games
triathlon course in Sydney was approved by the International
Olympic Committee (IOC) on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Scenic course in and around Sydney's famous harbour and
Opera House was the setting for International Triathlon Union
(ITU) World Cup races for men and women and it was not only the
competitors that were under scrutiny, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The course begins with a 1,500-metee swim in Farm Cove next to
the photogenic Opera House, a 40km bike leg lapping a route from
the Opera House around the harbour foreshores followed by a 10km
run through the city's streets and the Botanic Gardens.
</P>
<P>
Triathlon makes its Olympic debut at the 2000 Games, where it
may be the first event staged, and it received a boost with a
glowing commendation Sunday amid balmy spring conditions and
strong competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
