<HEADLINE> 16 People Burnt to Death in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 26 (Xinhua)-- At least 16 people were burnt
to death in a fire which broke out after a collision between two
vehicles in Tamil Nadu of southern India today, Press Trust of
India (PTI) said here.
</P>
<P>
The diesel tank of one of the vehicles exploded after the
collision, resulting in the fire, it quoted police as saying.
</P>
<P>
The bodies were charred and mutilated beyond recognition.
</P>
<P>
Eight people were admitted to a city hospital for treatment. As
many as 28 people were traveling in the two vehicles when the
mishap occurred.  
</P>
