<DOCNO> XIE19971026.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Xiaolangdi Water Control Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The Yellow River, China's
second longest, is being blocked today for the multi-purpose dam
project at Xiaolangdi, in Henan province.
</P>
<P>
The project is the largest on the Yellow River and consists of
three parts: the dam, a water diversion and sediment system, and a
power plant.
</P>
<P>
The rockfill dam is 154 meters high and is 1,317 m. long.
</P>
<P>
The total storage capacity of the reservoir is 12.65 billion
cu.m., and is second only to the Three Gorges
reservoir. Ninety-three percent of the Yellow River's
694,000-sq.km. drainage area is located upstream from the
Xiaolangdi Dam site.
</P>
<P>
The main purpose of the project is control of flood, ice and
silt, water supply, and power generation. It will prevent the
sorts of floods that occur every thousand years while existing
facilities can only cope the lesser ones that occur every 60 years
like those that occurred recently.
</P>
<P>
Xiaolangdi has been considered one of the most challenging jobs
in the history of engineering because of the 16 tunnels and the
generating plant that are to be built under a sandy hill on the
northern bank.
</P>
<P>
Construction work started in September, 1994 and will be
completed by 2001. It will cost 40 billion yuan, 1.1 billion US
dollars worth of funds coming from World Bank loans. Bids for the
work came in from all over the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971026.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Second Longest River Starts To Be Dammed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI, October 26 (Xinhua) -- Damming operations have
started for the Xiaolangdi Water Control Project in Luoyang in
Henan Province on the Yellow River, China's second longest.
</P>
<P>
At 16:15, six trucks, side by side on the river's southern
bank, simultaneously dumped the first load of stones into the
river.
</P>
<P>
The damming will take 42 hours to complete. Chinese and foreign
engineers and laborers will work round-the-clock at the end of the
dam.
</P>
<P>
The flow of the river at present is suitable for damming,
according to the chief engineer.
</P>
<P>
The Xiaolangdi Project will be the largest water control
project on the Yellow River and the second largest reservoir in
China. China already has 160 reservoirs on the Yellow River for
flood prevention. 
</P>
</TEXT>
