<HEADLINE> OAU Military Meeting Hailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The second OAU chiefs of
defense meeting has provided an information sharing forum in the
search for pragmatic strategies for managing and resolving
conflicts in Africa, a Zimbabwean defense official said.
</P>
<P>
Vitalis Zvinavashe, Commander of Zimbabwean Defense Forces
made the remarks at a press conference marking the end of the
two-day meeting of the chiefs of defense of the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) central organ last night.
</P>
<P>
He said Africa has the largest number of intra-state
conflicts. The Organization of African Unity maintained that it
is beneficial to invest in preventing conflicts than spend
considerable resources in putting out fires among us, he added.
</P>
<P>
He noted that some of our countries spent huge amounts of
resources waging war, and yet were reluctant or unwilling to
contribute towards maintaining peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
He said Africa has a problem of funding peacekeeping efforts
and will soon undertake activities to raise funds and establish a
peace fund if resolutions adopted at the meeting are endorsed by
the political leaders at their November meeting in Addis Ababa,
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
OAU Assistant Political Director Sam Ibok said once endorsed,
the organization will organize a peace week, launch a
commemorative stamp in each country, football matches among
popular football teams in Africa as way of raising funds
throughout the continent for the peace fund.
</P>
<P>
The meeting discussed issues relating to command and control,
logistics, finance, communications, training, doctrine, structure
and operation planning for the OAU peace support operations.
</P>
</TEXT>
