<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin, Core of China's Leadership of Third Generation (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Even though China's political situation has become more stable,
its economy prospered and people's living standards improved day
by day, Jiang as China's top leader has never been intoxicated
with the successes, and has constantly exhorted leading carders at
all levels: "We should have the awareness of hardships and think
of danger in times of safety."
</P>
<P>
With regard to the contradictions and difficulties existing in
economic and social life, he always keeps a clear head and exerts
himself to resolve them.
</P>
<P>
In the past eight years or more, he has traveled to all of
China's provinces (except Taiwan), autonomous regions and
municipalities directly under the Central Government, and gone
deep into grassroots units for investigation and study as well as
for the understanding of social conditions and popular will.
</P>
<P>
Wherever he goes, he will invariably visit those workers whose
enterprises have not extricated themselves from difficult
positions, and express his sincere solicitude.
</P>
<P>
He pays special attention to the life of those people who live
in poor areas of remote provinces. The Chinese Government under
his direction worked out a very ambitious "plan to alleviate
poverty" and was determined to accomplish in the main the task of
providing adequate food and clothing for the impoverished people
in rural areas within this century. During the past five years,
the rural poor population of the country has decreased by 32
million.
</P>
<P>
In the diplomatic field, the third generation of collective
leadership with Jiang at the core has demonstrated its outstanding
capability to cope with the international situation and handle all
kinds of complex international affairs.
</P>
<P>
In the past eight years under his leadership, China has scored
a series of diplomatic successes. China's international standing
has risen increasingly and its influence on international affairs
has kept growing.
</P>
<P>
China's relations with all countries in the world have further
developed on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful
Coexistence. The good-neighborly relations with the surrounding
countries have been further consolidated, and solidarity and
cooperation with the vast number of developing countries have been
greatly strengthened.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government attaches great importance to Sino-US
relations, and in meeting with US personages of political and
various circles, Jiang has reiterated again and again the
standpoint to increase trust, reduce trouble, develop co-operation
and provoke no confrontation. This standpoint has met with
approval from people of insight of various circles in the United
States.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
