<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin, Core of China's Leadership of Third Generation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 26 (Xinhua) -- In China, people generally
address Jiang Zemin as "the core of the leadership of the third
generation", because in the people's eyes, Jiang is the top leader
succeeding Mao Zedong and Deng Xiaoping, the cores of China's
leadership of the first and second generations respectively.
</P>
<P>
Just at the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) which concluded recently, he was re-elected General
Secretary of the Central Committee of CPC, the ruling party with
58 million members, thus continuing to take on the historical
mission of leading the world's most populous country to advance to
the 21st century. Jiang's re-election is the common aspiration of
the people and enjoys popular confidence.
</P>
<P>
In the past eight years since Jiang assumed the office of
China's top leader, China has been stable socially and
politically, its economy has continued to develop, its national
strength has been continuously enhanced, its government has been
extremely active diplomatically and the people's living standards
have risen steadily.
</P>
<P>
During this period, the gross domestic product (GDP) grew at an
average annual rate of about 12 percent. Not only did the economy
undergo a rapid growth, but inflation was brought under effective
control. It is the common desire of the Chinese people of all
ethnic groups to maintain the current momentum of development.
</P>
<P>
What remains fresh in people's memory is that during the
political disturbances occurring successively at home and abroad
in the late 1980s and early 1990s, Jiang remained unruffled in the
face of turmoil and coped with the situation calmly in the manner
of a statesman who "remains calm before the collapse of Mount
Taishan".
</P>
<P>
With the support of Deng Xiaoping, the chief architect of
China's reforms and opening up, Jiang took a series of measures to
keep the political situation stable, and lost no time to carry
forward the reforms and open China even wider to the outside
world.
</P>
<P>
Not only did he hold his ground, but also there emerged
throughout the country a flourishing trend toward economic and
social development. He himself has thus built up his image and
prestige among the Chinese people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
