<HEADLINE> Thai King Wants Fast Passage of Organic Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 26 (Xinhua) -- King Bhumibol Adulyadej has
urged the Thai government and parliament to speed up the passage
of three organic laws related to general elections, so that the
country could go to the polls under the new constitution.
</P>
<P>
The king told some cabinet members on Saturday: "it is your
duty to make sure the completion of the new constitution happens
as soon as possible," according to the Nation Daily today.
</P>
<P>
Under the new constitution, three organic laws -- on the
electoral system, political parties and the election commission,
must be ready within eight months after the promulgation of the
new constitution on October 11.
</P>
<P>
The new constitution has been hailed as a major step toward
political reform and elimination of money politics in the country.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh
promised quick passage of the supplementary laws.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the whole process of adopting the three
laws, if put on fast track, would take only one to two months, and
a House dissolution would be announced by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Deputy interior minister Likit Thiravegin said the elections
would take place sometime in January.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
