<HEADLINE> Trade Relations Between Brazil, Europe Improved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Vice-president Marco
Antonio de Oliveira Maciel said here Friday that trade relations
of his country with Europe, and especially with Spain, have
improved.
</P>
<P>
De Oliveira made the remarks at the closing ceremony of a
seminar on Brazil.
</P>
<P>
He said that trade between Brazil and Spain doubled in the last
three years.
</P>
