<HEADLINE> Romania to Start Winter Time Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 25 (Xinhua) -- Romania will start winter
time 00:00 a.m. Sunday and people will set their clocks back by
one hour.
</P>
<P>
From this year, Romania will end summer time the last Sunday of
October in a bid to keep up with the European Union's timing,
which will be put into use tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
In the past, Romania suspended summer time one month earlier
than the European Union countries.
</P>
<P>
There is a three-hour difference between the Romanian time and
the Greenwich mean time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
