<HEADLINE> Brazil to Distribute Vaccine Against Hepatitis B </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Brazil will distribute
vaccine doses against hepatitis B across the country starting from
November.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian National Epidemiology Center Director, Jarbas Barbosa,
said today that more than 12 million doses of the vaccine will
be distributed in November alone.
</P>
<P>
The official said hepatitis B is ravaging the northern states
of Mato Grosso, Espiritu Santo, Roraima and Santa Catarina.
</P>
<P>
Hepatitis B is transmitted through sex acts, blood transfusion,
and pregnancy. The country has decided to vaccinate groups of
higher risk first, especially prostitutes.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics showed that some 12,000 Brazilians have
contracted hepatitis B over the past two years and 10 percent of
them develop liver cancer or hepatic cyrrhosis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
