<HEADLINE> Motor Vehicles Double in Colombia in Ten Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The number of motor
vehicles in Colombia almost doubled in just 10 years, going from
1.286 million to 2.331 million.
</P>
<P>
In addition, there are 1.062 million motorcycles, the Traffic
Prevention Union told the seventh assembly of the Colombian
Insurers Union today.
</P>
<P>
The number of vehicles rose from 42.07 to 58.82 per 1,000
people during the period between 1986 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
However, traffic accidents have shown a reducing trend with
deaths diminishing noticeably, the union said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
