<HEADLINE> Eldredge Overcomes Injury to Win at Skate America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 25 (Xinhua) -- American skater Todd
Eldredge overcame his shoulder injuries to win the men's
competition at Skate America International in Detroit on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Eldredge hit a chunk of ice and crashed into the boards in the
warmups, which led to the separation in his shoulders.
</P>
<P>
Russian Evgeni Plushenko won the silver medal and his
countrymen Alexander Abt won the bronze.
</P>
<P>
In the pairs final, U.S. skater Jason Dungjen dislocated his
thumb, but skated an excellent program to win the silver medal
with his partner Kyoko Ina.
</P>
<P>
Marina Eltsova and Andrey Bushkov of Russia claimed the gold
medal in pairs and their compatriots Evgenia Shishkova and Vadim
Naumov won the bronze medal. 
