<HEADLINE> Kong to Clash Primorac in Table Tennis World Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 25 (Xinhua) -- 1995 world champion Kong Linghui
of table tennis powerhouse China will be fighting for his second
major international singles title against Zoran Primorac of
Croatia at the 1997 Table Tennis World Cup in Nimes, France.
</P>
<P>
Kong took a sweet revenge over Vladimir Samsonov of Belarus,
who beat him in this April's World Championships semi-finals at
Manchester, with a 21-18, 21-16, 17-21, 21-11 victory.
</P>
<P>
Before his semi triumph over the world number three Samsonov,
Kong swept away current world champion Jan-Ove Waldner of Sweden
21-8, 21-17, 21-12 in a mere 25-minute quarter-final showdown.
</P>
<P>
The Croatian Primorac, after knocking out Kim Taek Soo of South
Korea 21-16, 21-19, 21-16 in the top eight clash, produced a
straight sets 21-19, 21-18, 21-19 victory over the home favourite
Christophe Legout in the other semi-final battle.
</P>
<P>
Legout had earlier come back from two sets down to upset German
Jorg Rosskopf 16-21, 18-21, 21-19, 23-21, 21-17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
