<HEADLINE> Korda to Face Krajicek in Stuttgart Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 25 (Xinhua) -- Petr Korda of the Czech Republic
upset U.S. Open champion Patrick Rafter of Australia 6-4, 7-6 on
Saturday to set up a Stuttgart Open tennis final showdown with
1996 Wimbledon champion Richard Krajicek.
</P>
<P>
Korda reached his third final of the season by outclassing the
third seed Rafter, who had failed to reach the final for only the
second time in the last six tournaments.
</P>
<P>
Krajicek, who eliminated world number one Pete Sampras of the
United States and defending champion Boris Becker of Germany on
his march to the final, added 13th seed Jonas Bjorkman to his
victims 6-4, 3-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The 16th seed Dutchman was crowned the title here in 1995.
</P>
</TEXT>
