<HEADLINE> Chinese Paddlers Win Doubles Champion in Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese double players Li Ju
and Wang Nan today won the first Lebanese international Women
Table Tennis Open title after beating another Chinese double
players Wang Hui and Cheng Hongxia.
</P>
<P>
The two Chinese pairs entered the final after defeating
their opponents from Canada and Mylaysia.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese players dominated today's matches at the Mont La
Salle stadium here.
</P>
<P>
In the women's semi-finals, China's Wang Nan, ranked 3 in the
world and Wang Hui, ranked 18 respectively edged their Malaysian
and Chinese opponents and entered the final which will be played
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The four-day tournament, which started on Friday, was attended
by 30 players from 11 contries, including China, Canada, Malaysia,
Lebanon, Ukraine and France. 
